  "text": "From Figure 3 we see that the phase of the initial conditions has an important influence on the overall growth involved in passage through a single resonance tongue. In [CITATION_1] , this growth effect has been called amplification. Note that while most initialcondition phases lead to an increase in amplitude, there is a small range of values close to 3 279558 which lead to de-amplification. Finally we note from Figure 4 , that the amplification is dependent on the magnitude of the parametric excitation, 4. The graph is not monotonically increasing1 there are a series of local maxima and minima. The reason for this phenomenon, which was not examined in [CITATION_2] , will be discussed later on in this paper.",
